page.title: 06FOOTBALL & SOCIAL CLUB
page.content:
In the early 1970's the{Eton Wick {Community}wanted a Sports and Social activity. Mr Jarrat(the president)and three colleagues got the money to build the club by running the annual Wicko Carnival. In 1972 it was completed.
The Social Club today has 1,155 members 60% live in Eton Wick.The Club has live music, a crib team, four men's football teams, two darts teams, over 60's club, blood transfusion service and links with junior football of the youth club. A years membership is Â£2.00.
{Mr Jarrat}would like to see junior football use the Club more he wants to see more sports and social activities develop.
